properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 14 at 12:38AM CST until January 14 at 9:00AM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
...ACCUMULATING SNOW THIS MORNING...

.A potent, but fast-moving, system will pass through the region
this morning, which will bring widespread accumulating snow to
the Northland. The heaviest snow is anticipated to fall along the
North Shore tonight, thanks to lake enhanced snowfall due to
persistent southerly winds. Additionally, heavier snowfall amounts
are expected from Koochiching County into northern St. Louis
county. Some freezing drizzle may mix in at times during the early
morning hours Tuesday, but snow will be the primary threat.

* WHAT...Snow. Additional snow accumulations of 1 to 3 inches.

* WHERE...North St. Louis and Koochiching Counties. This
includes the Tribal Lands of the Bois Forte Band, Nett Lake
area.

* WHEN...Until 9 AM CST this morning.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
Road conditions can also be found at 511mn.org for Minnesota or
511wi.gov for Wisconsin.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 AM CST THIS MORNING
